      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While high-dose vitamin D supplements like 50,000 IU are sometimes prescribed by doctors for specific deficiency cases, you should not self-prescribe such a massive and prolonged dose because it carries a significant risk of serious toxicity, which can damage your kidneys and liver. Excessive intake causes symptoms like nausea, weakness, and calcium imbalances, and without blood work monitoring, it is impossible to know exactly how much your body can absorb safely. Instead, consult a healthcare provider in Oslo for a simple blood test to determine your current levels so they can prescribe the right, safe dosage tailored to you.",
