      "content": "Alternating doses like 50,000 IU every other day is dangerous because your body continuously absorbs fat-soluble vitamins regardless of the schedule, leading to a rapid total accumulation that can still cause toxicity within a month. Even on an \"every other day\" regimen, ingesting such amounts for an extended period usually risks severe hypercalcemia, kidney stones, or acute kidney injury without prior blood tests. The safest immediate action is to visit an Oslo clinic for a rapid 25(OH)D blood test to get a precise prescription that matches your specific deficiency rather than guessing with supersupplements.",
